es in inventory.", "\"SALES ASSUMPTIONS\":\"Sales assumptions are the underlying assumptions about future sales levels used in planning and forecasting.\"", "\"FIXED PRODUCT MIX\":\"Fixed product mix refers to a consistent combination of different products that a company sells.\"", "\"BREAKEVEN ANALYSIS\":\"Breakeven analysis is the process of determining the breakeven point, where total revenue equals total costs.\"", "\"PLANNING AND DECISION MAKING\":\"Planning and decision making involve the process of setting objectives and determining the best course of action to achieve them.\"", "\"FINANCIAL GAIN\":\"Financial gain is the increase in monetary value that results from business activities.\"", "\"EXPENSES\":\"Expenses are the economic costs that a business incurs through its operations to earn revenue.\"", "\"COSTS\":\"Costs refer to the monetary valuation of effort, material, resources, time, and utilities consumed to produce a good or service.\"", "\"TAXES\":\"Taxes are compulsory financial charges imposed on individuals or entities by a governmental organization.\"", "\"BUSINESS EXPENSES\":\"Business expenses are the costs incurred in the ordinary course of business.\"", "\"LEVEL OF OUTPUT\":\"Level of output is the quantity of goods or services produced by a company.\"", "\"PRIMARY OPERATIONS\":\"Primary operations are the main activities that generate revenue for a company.\"", "\"GRAPHICAL REPRESENTATION\":\"Graphical representation is the visual display of data using plots and charts.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}